1
00:00:00,600 --> 00:00:02,167
My proposal was approved.

2
00:00:02,400 --> 00:00:04,267
I'll be leaving for Hong Kong
next month.

3
00:00:04,267 --> 00:00:06,100
You really want to study
migratory birds?

4
00:00:06,100 --> 00:00:08,033
I've always wanted
to study ornithology.

5
00:00:08,167 --> 00:00:11,467
I only became a teacher
to fund my studies.

6
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:13,767
Did you receive
your sister's invitation?

7
00:00:13,900 --> 00:00:14,967
I'm sorry, Ma.

8
00:00:15,133 --> 00:00:16,600
I won't be able
to come home yet.

9
00:00:16,733 --> 00:00:19,533
You need to be at
your sister's wedding.

10
00:00:19,667 --> 00:00:21,300
Princess, talk to her.

11
00:00:21,433 --> 00:00:23,433
If she doesn't want to come,
don't force her.

12
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:25,133
We'll be fine without her.

13
00:00:25,267 --> 00:00:27,633
I need you to
focus on Grace Banaag.

14
00:00:27,800 --> 00:00:29,067
She's a bit problematic.

15
00:00:29,167 --> 00:00:31,900
I hope you can help her.

16
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:33,800
My name is Ms. Anna Sarmiento.

17
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:36,733
I'm the substitute teacher
for Ma'am Thelma Reyes.

18
00:00:36,867 --> 00:00:39,467
I would like to speak
with your parents.

19
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:40,567
Ma...

20
00:00:40,700 --> 00:00:42,167
What is it?
I don't have any money.

21
00:00:42,300 --> 00:00:44,567
My teacher just wants
to talk to you.

22
00:00:44,667 --> 00:00:46,167
What did you
do again this time?

23
00:00:46,300 --> 00:00:47,767
Just make something up.
I don't want to.

24
00:00:48,633 --> 00:00:49,500
This is the food?

25
00:00:49,667 --> 00:00:50,900
That's all we have.

26
00:00:51,533 --> 00:00:53,000
You think you're
so tough now, huh?!

27
00:00:53,167 --> 00:00:55,800
Do you want me
pluck your eyes out?!

28
00:00:55,933 --> 00:00:57,633
Just go. Ah! Grace!

29
00:00:58,667 --> 00:00:59,767
- What?!
- Chito!

30
00:00:59,867 --> 00:01:02,633
Discipline your daughter!
Look how rude she is!

31
00:01:05,833 --> 00:01:12,667
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

32
00:01:54,100 --> 00:02:01,167
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

33
00:02:04,700 --> 00:02:05,700
Grace!

34
00:02:05,833 --> 00:02:08,500
What are you doing?!
My lipstick's expensive!

35
00:02:08,600 --> 00:02:10,733
Stop playing with it!
Put it back where it was!

36
00:02:10,867 --> 00:02:12,567
Put it back!

37
00:02:12,700 --> 00:02:14,200
I said put it back!

38
00:02:17,767 --> 00:02:18,767
What?

39
00:02:18,933 --> 00:02:20,533
It doesn't hurt anymore, right?

40
00:02:21,200 --> 00:02:22,667
It doesn't hurt anymore, Ma.

41
00:02:23,100 --> 00:02:25,067
Don't worry.

42
00:02:25,200 --> 00:02:27,400
Once I make some money,

43
00:02:27,533 --> 00:02:29,433
I'll take you to the fair.

44
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:31,400
Who knows? You might win again.

45
00:02:31,533 --> 00:02:33,767
I'll buy you a chick
so Pipo can have a playmate.

46
00:02:34,300 --> 00:02:35,733
Really, Ma?

47
00:02:35,867 --> 00:02:39,200
Do I need to repeat myself?
I just said I will, didn't I?

48
00:02:39,300 --> 00:02:41,533
I'll take you there
as long as you behave.

49
00:02:41,633 --> 00:02:43,500
The problem with you
is you don't listen.

50
00:02:43,633 --> 00:02:45,267
Don't be naughty when
your Uncle Chito is around,

51
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:46,900
especially when he's
had some drinks.

52
00:02:47,600 --> 00:02:50,067
But, Mama, I'm not naughty.

53
00:02:50,167 --> 00:02:52,300
Uncle Chito is just scary,

54
00:02:52,433 --> 00:02:55,033
especially when he
glares like this.

55
00:02:55,600 --> 00:02:57,633
See? You're doing it again.

56
00:02:57,767 --> 00:03:00,800
You keep getting in trouble
because you always do that.

57
00:03:00,933 --> 00:03:03,567
I'm not doing anything wrong.

58
00:03:03,667 --> 00:03:06,633
We're lucky that he's
helping us raise you.

59
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:08,633
I'm grown up, Ma.

60
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:10,300
I'll help you.

61
00:03:10,467 --> 00:03:12,300
My goodness, stop it.

62
00:03:12,433 --> 00:03:14,300
Your Uncle Chito loves me
very much.

63
00:03:14,467 --> 00:03:16,300
You know I gave birth to you
when I was only 15,

64
00:03:16,467 --> 00:03:19,633
and your bastard of a father
died too soon, right?

65
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:22,800
We wouldn't have survived
if not for your Uncle Chito.

66
00:03:23,700 --> 00:03:26,667
I'm so happy to be
with your Uncle Chito.

67
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:30,433
I wouldn't know what I'd do
if he left us.

68
00:03:30,533 --> 00:03:32,500
I wouldn't be able to bear it.
I might die.

69
00:03:33,300 --> 00:03:34,967
I love you, Mama.

70
00:03:35,100 --> 00:03:39,000
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

71
00:03:39,133 --> 00:03:41,433
You love me too, right?

72
00:03:41,533 --> 00:03:43,133
[SARAH] Here's some money.

73
00:03:43,267 --> 00:03:44,733
That should last you
until dinner.

74
00:03:45,867 --> 00:03:48,433
That's enough for you.
Just buy what you want.

75
00:03:49,033 --> 00:03:49,833
I'm leaving.

76
00:03:49,967 --> 00:03:56,833
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

77
00:04:03,733 --> 00:04:05,600
[GRACE SINGING]
 La la la la la

78
00:04:05,733 --> 00:04:08,133
[GRACE] Mister! Mister!
Please buy some.

79
00:04:08,233 --> 00:04:09,433
[MAN] That doesn't taste good.

80
00:04:09,567 --> 00:04:12,300
[GRACE] I'm positive
that this tastes good!

81
00:04:12,900 --> 00:04:15,600
[GRACE SINGING]
 La la la la la

82
00:04:15,733 --> 00:04:17,300
[MAN] Alright. You got me
with your cuteness.

83
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:18,700
- Here you go.
- Thank you, mister!

84
00:04:18,833 --> 00:04:19,833
You're so kind.

85
00:04:20,633 --> 00:04:21,600
Yes!

86
00:04:21,733 --> 00:04:24,367
Miss! Miss! Please buy some.

87
00:04:24,533 --> 00:04:26,867
Hey, Grace!
What's on your face?

88
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,533
Why are you wearing lipstick?

89
00:04:28,733 --> 00:04:31,900
Aren't you too young
to be using makeup?

90
00:04:32,367 --> 00:04:34,700
[WAITER] Hello, ma'am.
Can I get your order?

91
00:04:35,667 --> 00:04:36,900
Hotdog, fried rice, and egg.

92
00:04:37,767 --> 00:04:40,300
You're just jealous
because I'm pretty.

93
00:04:40,433 --> 00:04:41,633
[CHUCKLING]

94
00:04:41,767 --> 00:04:44,900
You know how to
clap back now, huh?

95
00:04:45,033 --> 00:04:46,500
Well, I'm no longer surprised.

96
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:48,900
She probably learned that
from her mother.

97
00:04:49,033 --> 00:04:50,567
- Let's go.
- Come on.

98
00:04:51,833 --> 00:04:52,233
[GRUNTS]
[YELPS]

99
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:53,300
You little rascal!

100
00:04:53,433 --> 00:04:57,667
[GIGGLING]
[PLAYFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

101
00:04:57,767 --> 00:04:59,400
[PANTING]

102
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:06,767
Are they gone?

103
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:10,433
What you did to her was wrong.

104
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:13,100
I was just joking around.

105
00:05:14,433 --> 00:05:16,333
Are you alone, Teacher?

106
00:05:18,300 --> 00:05:24,167
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

107
00:05:24,300 --> 00:05:25,900
Come this way, Teacher.

108
00:05:26,033 --> 00:05:27,767
It's cooler here.

109
00:05:30,133 --> 00:05:31,433
Hmm?

110
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:34,867
You're right, Teacher.
It really is cooler here.

111
00:05:37,233 --> 00:05:38,367
Here's your order, ma'am.

112
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:39,733
Thank you.

113
00:05:42,333 --> 00:05:45,033
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

114
00:05:45,167 --> 00:05:46,767
Is that yummy?

115
00:05:46,900 --> 00:05:48,367
Is that bright?

116
00:05:49,967 --> 00:05:50,700
Bright?

117
00:05:50,833 --> 00:05:52,100
Like the one in the commercial.

118
00:05:52,233 --> 00:05:53,067
Bright hotdog.

119
00:05:53,167 --> 00:05:55,967
The hotdog of bright kids!

120
00:05:56,100 --> 00:05:58,633
I don't know. I don't cook it.

121
00:05:59,100 --> 00:06:00,133
What does it taste like?

122
00:06:00,267 --> 00:06:02,967
Bright hotdog
has cheese inside.

123
00:06:03,100 --> 00:06:05,567
Or is that one chicken-flavored?

124
00:06:06,467 --> 00:06:09,267
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

125
00:06:09,433 --> 00:06:11,167
Didn't you eat at home?

126
00:06:12,267 --> 00:06:13,233
I did.

127
00:06:13,367 --> 00:06:15,100
Actually, that's what
I ate earlier.

128
00:06:15,200 --> 00:06:17,167
Mama cooked it for me.

129
00:06:17,267 --> 00:06:19,467
But it's been hours
since I last ate.

130
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:22,333
Then go back home
so you can eat again.

131
00:06:22,467 --> 00:06:23,967
Uh...

132
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:26,967
I ate all our hotdogs.

133
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:30,433
Mama might not be able
to buy more until tomorrow.

134
00:06:30,533 --> 00:06:34,500
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

135
00:06:35,167 --> 00:06:40,267
[STOMACH GROWLING]

136
00:06:40,367 --> 00:06:43,500
[CHUCKLING SHEEPISHLY]

137
00:06:52,867 --> 00:06:54,033
Thank you.

138
00:06:54,533 --> 00:06:56,133
Thank you, ma'am.

139
00:06:56,667 --> 00:06:58,000
You should learn
how to talk politely,

140
00:06:58,133 --> 00:07:00,133
especially when you're speaking
with someone older than you.

141
00:07:00,700 --> 00:07:02,667
Didn't your mother
teach you that?

142
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:06,133
Of course, she did... ma'am.

143
00:07:07,300 --> 00:07:10,500
Is it okay if my mother
just visits you tomorrow?

144
00:07:10,633 --> 00:07:12,967
You see, she has something
important to do today.

145
00:07:15,433 --> 00:07:16,733
Oh, what's the matter?

146
00:07:17,167 --> 00:07:18,900
Nothing. It's just hot.

147
00:07:19,067 --> 00:07:25,900
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

148
00:07:34,767 --> 00:07:38,500
Ma'am, how do you
spell the word bright?

149
00:07:39,667 --> 00:07:41,667
Why do you ask?

150
00:07:41,767 --> 00:07:44,167
I like writing down
the things that make me happy.

151
00:07:44,900 --> 00:07:48,700
So whenever I'm sad,
I just read them.

152
00:07:49,967 --> 00:07:54,500
My father used to say that
I should always stay positive!

153
00:07:55,767 --> 00:07:57,567
Where's your father now?

154
00:07:58,067 --> 00:08:01,267
My mother said
he's with the Lord now.

155
00:08:01,433 --> 00:08:03,600
How about you?
Where's your father?

156
00:08:05,467 --> 00:08:06,733
He's gone.

157
00:08:09,033 --> 00:08:11,500
Hold on. Why are you
asking so many questions?

158
00:08:12,300 --> 00:08:16,100
Ma'am Thelma said we shouldn't
hesitate to ask questions.

159
00:08:17,100 --> 00:08:22,867
Mama said Papa always
watches over me.

160
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:26,700
But why does it seem
like he doesn't do anything?

161
00:08:30,100 --> 00:08:32,600
Why? What do you want him
to do for you?

162
00:08:34,333 --> 00:08:36,133
Where do you live?

163
00:08:36,267 --> 00:08:38,100
Who do you live with?

164
00:08:39,500 --> 00:08:41,267
No one. I live alone.

165
00:08:42,300 --> 00:08:43,767
[GRACE]
Where's your mother?

166
00:08:43,900 --> 00:08:45,433
Why isn't she with you?

167
00:08:45,567 --> 00:08:47,567
Doesn't she love you?

168
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:50,967
As for me, my mother loves me.

169
00:08:51,100 --> 00:08:54,633
She doesn't like it when I leave
because she misses me a lot.

170
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:58,667
And she gives me money.

171
00:08:59,700 --> 00:09:01,400
Once you grow up,

172
00:09:01,533 --> 00:09:03,633
you can earn money
and live alone.

173
00:09:04,300 --> 00:09:06,500
You won't need to be
with her all the time.

174
00:09:06,633 --> 00:09:08,133
Is that how it works, ma'am?

175
00:09:08,267 --> 00:09:15,100
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

176
00:09:20,500 --> 00:09:22,300
[SARAH YAWNS]

177
00:09:26,433 --> 00:09:27,500
D*mn it.

178
00:09:27,667 --> 00:09:28,700
Grace.

179
00:09:31,133 --> 00:09:32,000
Grace!

180
00:09:34,833 --> 00:09:36,167
Grace, come here!

181
00:09:36,300 --> 00:09:38,367
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

182
00:09:38,533 --> 00:09:40,667
I just fed Pipo.

183
00:09:40,800 --> 00:09:43,267
My goodness, you brat.
Why is breakfast not ready yet?

184
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:44,600
See?!

185
00:09:44,733 --> 00:09:47,200
I'm starving to death here!

186
00:09:48,333 --> 00:09:50,000
I'm working, and you
expect me to do that too?!

187
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:53,033
D*mn it.

188
00:09:54,300 --> 00:09:55,533
D*mn that chicken.

189
00:09:56,233 --> 00:09:58,367
These damn bills
are in front of me

190
00:09:58,533 --> 00:10:00,667
instead of food!

191
00:10:03,067 --> 00:10:04,700
You better not do
this again, Grace!

192
00:10:04,833 --> 00:10:06,900
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

193
00:10:07,067 --> 00:10:08,667
- Who is it?
- [MAN] Sarah?

194
00:10:08,767 --> 00:10:09,967
[KNOCKING CONTINUES]

195
00:10:10,100 --> 00:10:11,133
[MAN] Sarah!

196
00:10:12,067 --> 00:10:13,667
I know you're inside, Sarah!

197
00:10:15,533 --> 00:10:16,967
- Come out!
- It's the loan shark!

198
00:10:17,100 --> 00:10:18,467
- [MAN] Pay your debt!
- What?

199
00:10:18,600 --> 00:10:20,167
Go hide! And be quiet!

200
00:10:21,167 --> 00:10:22,133
[MAN] Sarah!

201
00:10:23,433 --> 00:10:25,200
- Sarah!
- Get down!

202
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:26,400
Come out!

203
00:10:26,567 --> 00:10:27,733
Be quiet!

204
00:10:27,900 --> 00:10:33,367
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

205
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:35,200
Hey, go check outside.

206
00:10:35,367 --> 00:10:36,933
- Okay.
- [SARAH] Go!

207
00:10:48,867 --> 00:10:50,867
- Hey!
- Aah!

208
00:10:50,967 --> 00:10:52,267
[MAN] Come out and stop hiding!

209
00:10:53,300 --> 00:10:54,167
Come out!

210
00:10:54,300 --> 00:10:56,233
Uh... move aside, Grace.

211
00:10:56,367 --> 00:10:57,533
Boss...

212
00:10:57,633 --> 00:10:59,700
Please stop making a scene.

213
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:01,333
- I'll pay you next--
- No!

214
00:11:01,467 --> 00:11:02,667
That's what you always say!

215
00:11:03,367 --> 00:11:04,267
I'll just take your TV!

216
00:11:04,433 --> 00:11:05,900
- No!
- You can't stop me!

217
00:11:06,033 --> 00:11:10,033
- Don't take the TV, please.
- [GRACE] Don't take it, mister!

218
00:11:10,167 --> 00:11:12,700
Please don't take the TV,
mister!

219
00:11:12,833 --> 00:11:14,467
Boss, let's just talk this out.

220
00:11:14,633 --> 00:11:16,800
Come on, just hear me out.

221
00:11:16,967 --> 00:11:18,633
[ENGINE REVVING]
Mister...

222
00:11:18,767 --> 00:11:24,567
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

223
00:11:24,667 --> 00:11:25,433
Something's burning!

224
00:11:25,567 --> 00:11:27,267
Oh no! The food!

225
00:11:27,400 --> 00:11:28,300
Go check it!

226
00:11:28,433 --> 00:11:30,867
[OIL SIZZLING]

227
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:33,300
Oh my gosh!
What do we do?!

228
00:11:33,433 --> 00:11:35,867
- Wait! I don't know--
- What's going on?!

229
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:37,300
- Move aside!
- Ow!

230
00:11:38,667 --> 00:11:39,800
You idiots!

231
00:11:39,967 --> 00:11:41,100
[THUDS]
[SARAH] Oh!

232
00:11:42,833 --> 00:11:44,167
How did that happen?!

233
00:11:44,333 --> 00:11:47,633
I was cooking,
but the loan shark came--

234
00:11:47,767 --> 00:11:49,167
[SLAPS]
[SARAH] Aah! Grace!

235
00:11:49,300 --> 00:11:50,500
Your stupidity almost
burned us all!

236
00:11:50,633 --> 00:11:53,500
- [SARAH] That's enough!
- What?!

237
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:55,600
Sarah, I'm disciplining her.

238
00:11:55,700 --> 00:11:57,000
That's the problem with you.

239
00:11:57,133 --> 00:11:59,133
She almost burned us all down,
and you're taking her side?

240
00:11:59,267 --> 00:12:01,267
All I'm saying is you
don't have to hurt her.

241
00:12:01,367 --> 00:12:03,467
[CHITO] No! No!

242
00:12:05,033 --> 00:12:07,767
You don't want me
to discipline her?

243
00:12:07,867 --> 00:12:11,000
Then provide for yourselves
and surive on your own.

244
00:12:11,133 --> 00:12:13,433
You can do that, right?
Right?

245
00:12:13,533 --> 00:12:15,100
[SARAH] Chito, wait.

246
00:12:15,233 --> 00:12:17,533
- It's not like that.
- [CHITO] Feed yourselves!

247
00:12:17,700 --> 00:12:19,700
[SARAH] Let's talk this out.

248
00:12:19,833 --> 00:12:22,200
Don't be mad.

249
00:12:22,333 --> 00:12:27,433
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

250
00:12:27,567 --> 00:12:28,500
[SOBS]

251
00:12:36,300 --> 00:12:39,700
[BELL RINGING]

252
00:12:39,833 --> 00:12:46,933
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

253
00:13:13,567 --> 00:13:20,400
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

254
00:13:45,367 --> 00:13:51,867
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

255
00:14:09,767 --> 00:14:11,400
Don't you have any friends?

256
00:14:11,500 --> 00:14:13,467
[QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

257
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:14,533
Why?

258
00:14:15,900 --> 00:14:18,267
Because you're always alone.

259
00:14:20,633 --> 00:14:22,367
I'll just sit with you.

260
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:29,933
[CHILDREN LAUGHING
IN THE DISTANCE]

261
00:14:30,133 --> 00:14:32,000
Why don't you join
your classmates?

262
00:14:32,500 --> 00:14:34,300
If I do, no one will
sit here with you.

263
00:14:34,467 --> 00:14:41,300
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

264
00:14:46,267 --> 00:14:47,467
Don't you have any snacks?

265
00:14:48,800 --> 00:14:50,500
I'm already full.

266
00:14:50,633 --> 00:14:52,300
I ate a lot at home.

267
00:14:52,467 --> 00:14:55,933
Mama bought so many
Bright hotdogs.

268
00:14:56,633 --> 00:14:58,267
I ate them all up.

269
00:15:02,133 --> 00:15:09,133
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

270
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:12,633
[ANNA] Here. You can have this.

271
00:15:13,967 --> 00:15:15,967
Thank you, ma'am!
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

272
00:15:24,200 --> 00:15:25,767
Hey, what are you doing?

273
00:15:25,867 --> 00:15:27,267
Why don't you eat it now?

274
00:15:28,233 --> 00:15:30,867
I'll eat it later
so I can share it with Pipo.

275
00:15:31,833 --> 00:15:32,933
Pipo?

276
00:15:33,633 --> 00:15:35,667
Pipo is my pet chicken.

277
00:15:35,867 --> 00:15:39,533
Pipo used to be this small.

278
00:15:39,700 --> 00:15:42,500
But Pipo has grown so big now.

279
00:15:48,933 --> 00:15:51,633
Oh! I have something for you.

280
00:15:51,733 --> 00:15:55,133
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

281
00:15:55,233 --> 00:15:57,500
You can also write in there
the things that make you happy

282
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:59,867
so we can both be happy.

283
00:16:03,067 --> 00:16:04,200
Thank you.

284
00:16:07,033 --> 00:16:09,500
[BIRD CHIRPING]

285
00:16:09,800 --> 00:16:10,833
The bird!

286
00:16:11,300 --> 00:16:12,767
Wait! Don't touch it.

287
00:16:14,067 --> 00:16:16,533
[GRACE]
Why did she drop her baby?

288
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:19,667
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

289
00:16:19,767 --> 00:16:22,100
Maybe it's sick or injured,

290
00:16:22,233 --> 00:16:23,667
so it was removed from the nest.

291
00:16:26,300 --> 00:16:29,167
Doesn't the mother
love her baby?

292
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:34,600
Maybe she didn't want her other
babies to get affected, too.

293
00:16:36,200 --> 00:16:38,567
Poor baby bird.

294
00:16:40,200 --> 00:16:45,567
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

295
00:16:45,733 --> 00:16:49,200
Is the baby bird with God now,
just like our fathers?

296
00:16:54,067 --> 00:16:55,233
You better get going.

297
00:16:55,233 --> 00:16:57,533
Wash your hands first
before you return to class.

298
00:16:57,800 --> 00:16:58,767
Thank you...

299
00:17:00,433 --> 00:17:01,033
...ma'am!

300
00:17:01,167 --> 00:17:03,733
Teacher Anna, stay positive!

301
00:17:05,100 --> 00:17:06,200
Go now.

302
00:17:10,333 --> 00:17:12,100
Grace, you're a thief!

303
00:17:12,233 --> 00:17:14,867
- You stole from me!
- [GRACE] No, I didn't!

304
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:16,633
- You took my money!
- I'm innocent!

305
00:17:16,767 --> 00:17:18,267
- You're a liar and a thief!
- No, I'm not!

306
00:17:18,433 --> 00:17:19,833
Hey, stop it.
Let go of each other.

307
00:17:19,967 --> 00:17:21,800
That's enough. I said stop it!

308
00:17:21,933 --> 00:17:27,167
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

309
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:30,800
Sir, Grace stole my wallet.

310
00:17:30,933 --> 00:17:33,633
Sir, I didn't steal anything.

311
00:17:33,833 --> 00:17:35,167
You're a liar, Grace.

312
00:17:35,300 --> 00:17:38,000
I saw all the money in your bag.

313
00:17:38,133 --> 00:17:40,567
It's mine! That's my money!

314
00:17:40,667 --> 00:17:42,133
How is that possible?

315
00:17:42,300 --> 00:17:45,100
You can't even afford
to buy snacks.

316
00:17:45,200 --> 00:17:47,100
I saved up that money.

317
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:50,667
No one believes you
because you're a liar!

318
00:17:50,833 --> 00:17:51,967
That's enough.

319
00:17:52,067 --> 00:17:53,333
Stop fighting.

320
00:17:54,033 --> 00:17:56,200
I've called for your parents.

321
00:17:56,333 --> 00:17:58,500
Let's wait for them to arrive.

322
00:17:59,400 --> 00:18:01,533
Go back to your classroom.

323
00:18:02,833 --> 00:18:03,800
Alright.

324
00:18:03,967 --> 00:18:05,467
Come on.

325
00:18:05,567 --> 00:18:10,433
[GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

326
00:18:10,500 --> 00:18:11,467
That's mine!

327
00:18:11,567 --> 00:18:12,433
This is mine!

328
00:18:12,533 --> 00:18:13,333
That's mine!

329
00:18:13,500 --> 00:18:15,133
- This is mine!
- Stop it.

330
00:18:15,800 --> 00:18:16,867
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

331
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:18,633
Grace?

332
00:18:18,733 --> 00:18:20,000
Grace.

333
00:18:20,167 --> 00:18:21,600
- Grace? Grace!
- Grace?

334
00:18:21,700 --> 00:18:22,667
Grace. Grace.

335
00:18:26,500 --> 00:18:27,833
I'll leave her in your care.

336
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:30,500
I have something to attend to.

337
00:18:31,900 --> 00:18:38,167
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

338
00:18:52,733 --> 00:18:53,833
Grace.

339
00:18:56,033 --> 00:18:58,700
The nurse said
you were hungry.

340
00:18:59,533 --> 00:19:01,367
My savings...

341
00:19:03,867 --> 00:19:05,733
[EXHALES SHARPLY, CLICKS MOUTH]

342
00:19:05,867 --> 00:19:07,233
Don't worry.

343
00:19:08,433 --> 00:19:09,367
Hmm.

344
00:19:11,100 --> 00:19:13,333
They've found
your classmate's wallet.

345
00:19:14,567 --> 00:19:16,567
I've also explained to them
that you have money

346
00:19:16,733 --> 00:19:18,533
because you're working.

347
00:19:22,067 --> 00:19:29,100
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

348
00:19:36,333 --> 00:19:40,233
You believe me?

349
00:19:46,767 --> 00:19:48,433
Go fix yourself up.

350
00:19:50,967 --> 00:19:52,133
Here.

351
00:19:53,667 --> 00:19:56,900
I bought you these.
Use them, okay?

352
00:20:00,667 --> 00:20:03,733
You know, you should
take a shower every day.

353
00:20:08,133 --> 00:20:11,467
Wake up early
so you can do that.

354
00:20:11,600 --> 00:20:13,900
Proper hygiene also makes you
free from diseases.

355
00:20:14,867 --> 00:20:21,767
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

356
00:20:24,133 --> 00:20:26,767
Don't forget
to use these, okay?

357
00:20:27,767 --> 00:20:28,900
Your hands are dirty.

358
00:20:38,800 --> 00:20:45,633
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

359
00:20:56,133 --> 00:20:58,133
Thank you.

360
00:20:58,300 --> 00:21:01,500
[CRYING]

361
00:21:01,667 --> 00:21:02,867
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

362
00:21:04,733 --> 00:21:05,767
[GRACE SNIFFLES]

363
00:21:09,933 --> 00:21:16,833
[MUSIC BECOMES MOROSE]

364
00:21:39,267 --> 00:21:40,333
Hey.

365
00:21:40,433 --> 00:21:42,000
This won't take long.

366
00:21:42,100 --> 00:21:45,700
Our principal said we should
just follow all the guidelines.

367
00:21:45,800 --> 00:21:48,333
Don't worry,
I'll do the talking, okay?

368
00:21:50,300 --> 00:21:53,200
[GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

369
00:21:53,367 --> 00:21:54,833
Whatever, Sarah!

370
00:21:54,933 --> 00:21:56,700
Every time I come here,
you always have a reason!

371
00:21:56,867 --> 00:21:58,100
I'll return tomorrow!

372
00:21:58,233 --> 00:22:00,867
If you still can't pay the rent,
just pack your stuff and go!

373
00:22:07,800 --> 00:22:10,367
Teacher, what are you
doing here?

374
00:22:10,467 --> 00:22:11,867
Uh, Grace.

375
00:22:12,967 --> 00:22:16,100
Grace, we just want
to talk to your mom.

376
00:22:16,933 --> 00:22:19,933
Why? Did my daughter
do something wrong?

377
00:22:20,100 --> 00:22:23,033
Hmm, maybe we should
talk about it inside.

378
00:22:24,633 --> 00:22:26,533
Okay. Please come in.

379
00:22:30,633 --> 00:22:36,700
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

380
00:22:36,800 --> 00:22:38,400
Buy some drinks for them.

381
00:22:39,900 --> 00:22:40,900
Hurry up.
Your teachers might be thirsty.

382
00:22:41,067 --> 00:22:42,900
[PATTY] Oh, no need.

383
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:47,600
[SARAH] Yes, Grace told me
she fainted at school.

384
00:22:47,767 --> 00:22:49,300
Don't worry about it.

385
00:22:49,467 --> 00:22:50,767
It's nothing.

386
00:22:50,933 --> 00:22:54,300
Maybe it was because
of iron deficiency, dear.

387
00:22:54,467 --> 00:22:57,400
You see, we have relatives
who are anemic.

388
00:22:57,500 --> 00:22:58,967
It's called "anemic," right?

389
00:22:59,133 --> 00:23:01,300
I'll cook some liver
for her later.

390
00:23:01,467 --> 00:23:02,100
[CHUCKLES AWKWARDLY]

391
00:23:02,267 --> 00:23:04,833
It's not just that, ma'am.

392
00:23:04,967 --> 00:23:07,800
We saw some bruises
on her body.

393
00:23:07,967 --> 00:23:09,267
- Bruises?
- [PATTY] Mm-hmm.

394
00:23:09,433 --> 00:23:12,300
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

395
00:23:12,467 --> 00:23:15,633
Is that right, dear?
You have bruises?

396
00:23:15,800 --> 00:23:18,267
Where? Let me see.

397
00:23:18,433 --> 00:23:19,300
Here?

398
00:23:22,533 --> 00:23:24,133
[SARAH] Oh.

399
00:23:24,300 --> 00:23:26,800
How did you get these bruises?

400
00:23:26,900 --> 00:23:27,933
Hmm?

401
00:23:28,033 --> 00:23:29,767
You got this while
playing at the park?

402
00:23:29,867 --> 00:23:32,267
You fell off the swing,
didn't you?

403
00:23:34,233 --> 00:23:36,367
Tsk. I warned you about this.

404
00:23:36,500 --> 00:23:40,000
I told you to stop playing
with the swing, remember?

405
00:23:40,167 --> 00:23:42,767
You'll just hurt yourself.

406
00:23:43,833 --> 00:23:48,433
[PATTY] Ma'am, Grace didn't get
those bruises from the swing.

407
00:23:48,533 --> 00:23:49,467
Oh.

408
00:23:50,367 --> 00:23:52,967
So, what are you
trying to imply?

409
00:23:53,133 --> 00:23:55,300
That I'm hurting
my daughter?

410
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:58,433
No, we're just looking out
for her.

411
00:24:00,200 --> 00:24:03,133
We just want to know how she's
doing when she's in the house.

412
00:24:03,233 --> 00:24:05,033
You assume she got it here?

413
00:24:05,200 --> 00:24:07,167
When a child has bruises,

414
00:24:07,333 --> 00:24:09,533
you'd blame the parents
immediately?

415
00:24:09,700 --> 00:24:14,333
Ma'am, my daughter spends
more time at school than here.

416
00:24:14,500 --> 00:24:17,867
Who knows? Maybe you're
hurting her at school.

417
00:24:18,033 --> 00:24:19,367
[PATTY] We're not hurting her.

418
00:24:19,533 --> 00:24:23,300
Grace, can you tell us
where you got those bruises?

419
00:24:24,033 --> 00:24:26,067
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

420
00:24:26,200 --> 00:24:29,167
At the park, ma'am.
I fell off the swing.

421
00:24:32,067 --> 00:24:36,267
My mom is a nice person.
She loves me.

422
00:24:36,633 --> 00:24:39,033
She doesn't hurt me.

423
00:24:39,200 --> 00:24:43,200
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

424
00:24:43,367 --> 00:24:44,267
So, um...

425
00:24:45,267 --> 00:24:47,067
We're good now, right?

426
00:24:47,233 --> 00:24:49,400
You heard my daughter.

427
00:24:51,367 --> 00:24:53,533
[SARAH] You can both go now.

428
00:24:53,633 --> 00:24:55,233
We're done here.

429
00:24:55,400 --> 00:24:56,400
- Oh.
- What's going on?

430
00:24:57,567 --> 00:24:58,933
What's this about?

431
00:24:59,067 --> 00:25:00,367
[SARAH] It's nothing, love.

432
00:25:00,467 --> 00:25:03,867
Grace's teachers just asked
some questions.

433
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:06,400
But they're leaving.
You're leaving, right?

434
00:25:07,600 --> 00:25:08,433
[PATTY] Let's go.

435
00:25:15,067 --> 00:25:22,067
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

436
00:25:35,500 --> 00:25:38,100
Her teachers came here
because she told on us.

437
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:40,000
Oh, wow! How amazing!

438
00:25:40,133 --> 00:25:42,067
You heard what the child said.

439
00:25:42,167 --> 00:25:43,267
She's still covering up
for her mom.

440
00:25:43,367 --> 00:25:45,767
In a world full of pain...

441
00:25:45,867 --> 00:25:47,333
Grace, if you ever
need anything,

442
00:25:47,467 --> 00:25:49,767
don't hesitate to
tell Teacher Patty.

443
00:25:49,933 --> 00:25:51,467
- Where are you going? Stop!
- Grace!

444
00:25:51,633 --> 00:25:53,767
How long will you endure?

445
00:25:53,867 --> 00:25:54,900
That's why I ate Pipo.

446
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:57,900
Don't you dare tell on us again.

447
00:25:58,000 --> 00:25:59,100
- You're so mean!
- Grace!

448
00:25:59,267 --> 00:26:01,233
You're fighting back, huh?

449
00:26:01,800 --> 00:26:02,600
[GRACE WHIMPERS]
